					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I've been reading the second of two snes manuals and in this book it first states that the SRAM on a Super Accelerator System is 2Mbyte, but later states that the maximum is only 2Mbit. <br />I assume that either I'm misreading something somewhere, or that the 2Mbyte is a typo, as the fullsnes doc only has a certain amount of sram address lines.<br />Can anyone clear this up for me?<br /><br />Thanks,<br />~Molive</div>

